author: Stahalamora
hideoutDescription:
Hello! I decided to make a Christmas Themed Hideout and the Glacial Hideout was the perfect base to use.

The snow is actually harder to cover up since the ground tends to be uneven, which is why I decided to incorporate it, rather than conceal it.

The decorations used are in keeping with the following master levels:

Zana - Lvl 7

Alva - Lvl 2

Niko - Lvl 4

Einhar - Lvl 4

Some of the decorations that I have used in this aren't available at these master levels but can be got by unlocking different hideouts and reclaiming the decorations in them. In used 762 hideout doodads in total to make this little snow village.
nameDescription: Christmas In Wraeclast - Glacial Hideout - Max Decorations - [Screenshots + Video]

author: Dark_Reaper115
hideoutDescription:
A hideout I had in standar for years where I would make a small area for each of the old masters...
Moved some stuff around for the new masters:

  • Einhar has a junglish looking corner with plentty of animals around
  • Zana to the left side near the map device
  • Jun in the middle cause I couldn't find a place big enough for her portals
  • Alva in a room full of books due to her historical knowledge
  • and finally Niko far away from everyone else with some injured exiles in a dark corner to the right.
